attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious botnet agent, likely a variant of Gafgyt or Mirai, targeting IoT devices. It exhibits several high-risk behaviors: it contains an exploit payload for Huawei Home Gateways using the TR-064 UPnP vulnerability ('/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1'), iterates through '/proc' to identify and kill competing malware processes, and communicates with a Command and Control (C2) server at IP '158.94.210.71'. Furthermore, it includes multiple specialized functions for launching Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks, such as TCP and UDP floods.
